data.title: Ucla Sigma Pi
data.meta_description: Sigma Pi is the oldest Fraternity at UCLA, founded in 1923.
data.text:
Since our inception on February 26, 1897, at Vincennes University in Indiana, Sigma Pi has grown into an international Fraternity which prides itself on brotherhood, scholarship, chivalry, and leadership. Our men strive for excellence by living our core values to promote fellowship, develop character, advance heightened moral awareness, enable academic achievement, and inspire service.

​

The Upsilon Chapter of Sigma Pi was founded in 1923, making it the oldest fraternity at UCLA. We are currently celebrating our 101st year at UCLA. The Upsilon Chapter is looking forward to continued years of success for its incoming members, actives, and alumni.

​

Please check out our most recent newsletter to get a taste of our fraternity and the brothers that make up the house!

​

​
